---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/use-cases" class="link text-sm">← Use-case playbooks</a>
      <span class="badge mt-6">Marketing stack playbook</span>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">Shopify marketing stack for {useCaseName}</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl text-cyan-100">{heroSubtitle}</p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg text-slate-300">Trigger: {trigger} · Timing: {timing}</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox title={`Stack picks for ${useCaseName}`} picks={tldrPicks} />
    <article class="prose-shopify mb-12 card">
      <h2>Stack execution playbook</h2>
  <p>Post-purchase education is the stack moment that reduces returns, support tickets, and buyer remorse — while setting up replenishment and cross-sell with correct timing. Pushing another sale before delivery on furniture, jewelry, or supplements increases returns and chargebacks.</p>
  <p>Immediate confirmation: order summary and expectation setting. Fulfillment: shipping notification. Education: delivery +2 days for usage, assembly, or routine guidance. Cross-sell: delivery +14 days for home goods, day 14 for consumables, day 7 for digital activation.</p>
  <p>Gift vs self-purchase branches mandatory — gift buyers get packaging and care content, not &quot;buy another for yourself.&quot; Shopify gift order properties or recipient-detected heuristics gate branches.</p>
  <p>Yotpo review request timing: delivery +5 to +14 days depending on category — after return window assessment for high-return SKUs. Experience language in supplements; fit and comfort in apparel.</p>
  <p>Marsello loyalty enrollment on second order or post-purchase email three after positive experience — not day-zero points pitch competing with product education.</p>
  <p>Recharge subscription first orders get onboarding education, not cross-sell conflicting with upcoming shipment. Subscription suppressions on replenishment promos in post-purchase path.</p>
  <p>AfterShip or Shopify delivery events gate cross-sell for home goods and high-AOV — cross-sell before delivery is top mistake in furniture stacks.</p>
  <p>Digital products: post-purchase IS activation — access link immediate, day 1/3/7 check-ins. No shipping modules. See digital vertical guide.</p>
  <p>SMS: delivery notification and delivery-day confirm for perishables — Postscript with opt-in. Not promotional cross-sell SMS.</p>
  <p>Analytics: review submission rate, second order within 60 days, support ticket reduction, cross-sell attach rate — each measured separately not blended.</p>

      <h2>Merchant scenarios</h2>
  <p><strong>Beauty routine post-purchase:</strong> Usage education day 2 → review day 7 → replenishment preview day 14 → loyalty enroll on 2nd order.</p>
  <p><strong>Furniture delivery-gated:</strong> Assembly email on delivered → review day 14 → cross-sell room completion day 21.</p>
  <p><strong>Gift jewelry order:</strong> Packaging care email → no cross-sell to gift buyer → recipient-focused content only.</p>
  <p><strong>Digital course:</strong> Access immediate → module 1 day 1 → stall help day 3 → no physical-product modules.</p>

      <h2>Stack checklist</h2>
      <ul>
    <li>Gift vs self branch configured</li>
    <li>Delivery-gated cross-sell for bulky SKUs</li>
    <li>Review request timed post-delivery appropriately</li>
    <li>Subscription first-order separate path</li>
    <li>Loyalty not in email one</li>
    <li>Education before cross-sell</li>
    <li>AfterShip trigger verified if used</li>
    <li>Support FAQ link in email one</li>
    <li>Replenishment preview timing documented</li>
    <li>SMS delivery-only if applicable</li>
    <li>Return window considered for review ask</li>
    <li>Second-order 60d metric tracked</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Exclusions (non-negotiable)</h3>
      <ul>
    <li>Gift purchasers (different messaging)</li>
    <li>Subscription first orders</li>
    <li>High-return SKUs needing fit guide first</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Metrics that prove quality</h3>
      <ul>
    <li>Review submission rate</li>
    <li>Second order within 60 days</li>
    <li>Support ticket reduction</li>
    <li>Cross-sell attach rate</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Common mistakes</h3>
      <ul>
    <li>Pushing another sale before delivery</li>
    <li>Same post-purchase for gifts and self-purchases</li>
    <li>No product-specific education</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Five-layer post-purchase stack map</h2>
  <div>
    <h3>Lifecycle orchestration: Sequenzy</h3>
    <p>Branched post-purchase by category and order type.</p>
    <p>Education → review → cross-sell sequence.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Cross-sell before delivery.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Cross-sell timestamp after delivery event.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Delivery intelligence: AfterShip, Shopify</h3>
    <p>Delivered trigger for timing accuracy.</p>
    <p>Furniture and bulky goods cross-sell gate.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Ordered-event triggers cross-sell.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> 100% bulky cross-sell post-delivery.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Proof layer: Yotpo</h3>
    <p>Timed review requests and UGC follow-up.</p>
    <p>Category-specific review timing.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Review ask before arrival.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Review rate by timing variant.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Loyalty enrollment: Marsello</h3>
    <p>Second-order or post-experience enrollment.</p>
    <p>Not competing with education email one.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Points pitch day zero.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Enrollment on 2nd order rate.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Analytics: Shopify</h3>
    <p>Second order 60d, tickets, review rate, cross-sell attach.</p>
    <p>Separate metrics per post-purchase email.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Blended post-purchase ROI.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Weekly metric dashboard exists.</p>
  </div>

      <h2>Timing and trigger governance</h2>
  <p>Confirmation: immediate.</p>
  <p>Education: delivery +2 days or digital day 1.</p>
  <p>Review ask: delivery +5 to +14 by category.</p>
  <p>Cross-sell: delivery +14 bulky, day 14 consumables.</p>
  <p>Loyalty enroll: second order trigger only.</p>

      <h2>Measurement across the stack</h2>
  <p>Review submission rate.</p>
  <p>Second order within 60 days.</p>
  <p>Support ticket volume per 100 orders.</p>
  <p>Cross-sell attach rate post-delivery.</p>
  <p>Return rate on post-purchase-influenced orders.</p>

      <h2>Related playbooks</h2>
  <p>Next: <a class="link" href="/use-cases/replenishment">replenishment</a> for consumables.</p>
  <p>Proof: <a class="link" href="/use-cases/reviews-and-ugc">reviews and UGC</a>.</p>
  <p>Vertical: <a class="link" href="/for/home-goods">home goods</a> delivery gating.</p>

<h2>Stack coordination for post-purchase education</h2>
<p>post-purchase education is not an email template problem — it is a stack handoff problem. Trigger: Order placed and payment confirmed Timing: Confirmation immediate; shipping at fulfillment; education at delivery +2 days; cross-sell at day 14 Every layer must read the same customer state: capture tags from Privy, lifecycle execution in Sequenzy, proof modules from Yotpo, loyalty tier from Marsello, SMS consent from Postscript. When reduce buyer anxiety and set up the next purchase, margin after discount matters more than attributed revenue.</p>
<p><strong>Lifecycle orchestration:</strong> Branched post-purchase by category and order type. Playbook fit: Education → review → cross-sell sequence. Failure mode: Cross-sell before delivery. Operator test: Cross-sell timestamp after delivery event.</p>
<p><strong>Delivery intelligence:</strong> Delivered trigger for timing accuracy. Playbook fit: Furniture and bulky goods cross-sell gate. Failure mode: Ordered-event triggers cross-sell. Operator test: 100% bulky cross-sell post-delivery.</p>
<p><strong>Proof layer:</strong> Timed review requests and UGC follow-up. Playbook fit: Category-specific review timing. Failure mode: Review ask before arrival. Operator test: Review rate by timing variant.</p>
<p><strong>Loyalty enrollment:</strong> Second-order or post-experience enrollment. Playbook fit: Not competing with education email one. Failure mode: Points pitch day zero. Operator test: Enrollment on 2nd order rate.</p>
<p><strong>Analytics:</strong> Second order 60d, tickets, review rate, cross-sell attach. Playbook fit: Separate metrics per post-purchase email. Failure mode: Blended post-purchase ROI. Operator test: Weekly metric dashboard exists.</p>
<p><strong>Scenario — Beauty routine post-purchase:</strong> Usage education day 2 → review day 7 → replenishment preview day 14 → loyalty enroll on 2nd order. Map this scenario to your vertical guide at /for if category-specific suppressions apply (Recharge tags, wholesale accounts, gift buyers).</p>
<p><strong>Scenario — Furniture delivery-gated:</strong> Assembly email on delivered → review day 14 → cross-sell room completion day 21. Map this scenario to your vertical guide at /for if category-specific suppressions apply (Recharge tags, wholesale accounts, gift buyers).</p>
<p><strong>Scenario — Gift jewelry order:</strong> Packaging care email → no cross-sell to gift buyer → recipient-focused content only. Map this scenario to your vertical guide at /for if category-specific suppressions apply (Recharge tags, wholesale accounts, gift buyers).</p>
<p><strong>Scenario — Digital course:</strong> Access immediate → module 1 day 1 → stall help day 3 → no physical-product modules. Map this scenario to your vertical guide at /for if category-specific suppressions apply (Recharge tags, wholesale accounts, gift buyers).</p>
